cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.DC 

The paper discusses network steganography, which involves hiding information in network traffic. This topic falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, since the paper focuses on the methods used for hiding information, rather than the specific applications or technologies involved, cs.CR and cs.NI are the most likely categories.
